local function findNth(str, pattern, n)
    local from = 0
    local to = 0
    while n > 0 do
        from, to = string.find(str, pattern, to+1)
        n = n - 1
    end
    return from, to
end

local function addBranch(url, branch)
  local from, to = findNth(url, "/", 5)
  return string.sub(url, 1, from) .. branch .. string.sub(url, to, string.len(url))
end

local function httpGet(url)
    local request=http.get(url)
    if request == nil and string.sub(url, 1, 34) == "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/" then
        -- try inserting /main/ as branch
        request = http.get(addBranch(url, "main"))
    end
    local content=request.readAll()
    request.close()
    return content
end

PKG_PATH="pkg"

local function checkDir()
    if not fs.exists(PKG_PATH) then
        fs.makeDir(PKG_PATH)
    end
    if not fs.isDir(PKG_PATH) then
        error(PKG_PATH .. " is not a directory")
    end
    if fs.isReadOnly(PKG_PATH) then
        error(PKG_PATH .. " is read-only")
    end
end


local function readFile(path)
    local fp = fs.open(path, "r")
    local data = fp.readAll()
    fp.close()
    return data
end

local function writeFile(path, data)
    local fp = fs.open(path, "w")
    fp.write(data)
    fp.close()
    return true
end

local function getLocalPkg(name)
    local path = PKG_PATH .. "/" .. name
    if not fs.exists(path) then
        return nil
    end
    return textutils.unserialise(readFile(path))
end

local function validatePkg(pkg)
    if type(pkg) ~= "table" or type(pkg.name) ~= "string" or type(pkg.version) ~= "string" then
        error("malformed package")
    end
    if (type(pkg.dst) == "string" and string.sub(pkg.dst, string.len(pkg.dst)) ~= "/") or pkg.dst ~= nil then
        error("invalid destination directory")
    end
end

local function pkgUrl(name)
    if string.sub(name, 1, 8) ~= "https://" then
        -- assume github
        return "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/" .. name
    else
        return name
    end
end

local function getRemotePkg(name)
    local baseUrl=pkgUrl(name)
    local pkg=textutils.unserialise(httpGet(baseUrl .. "/pkg"))
    validatePkg(pkg)
    pkg.baseUrl = baseUrl
    pkg.dst = pkg.dst or ""
    return pkg
end

local function canInstall(pkg)
    -- check files
    local overwrite = false
    for i = 1, #pkg.files do
        local path = pkg.dst .. pkg.files[i]
        if fs.exists(path) then
            print("! " .. path)
            overwrite = true
        end
    end
    return not overwrite
end

local function install(pkg)
    local files = {}
    print("Downloading " .. pkg.name .. " " .. pkg.version)
    for i = 1, #pkg.files do
        local file = pkg.files[i]
        local url = pkg.baseUrl .. "/" .. file
        files[file] = httpGet(url)
    end
    -- install
    print("Installing...")
    writeFile(PKG_PATH .. "/" .. pkg.name, textutils.serialise(pkg))
    for i = 1, #pkg.files do
        local file = pkg.files[i]
        local path = pkg.dst .. file
        if writeFile(path, files[path]) then
            print("+ " .. path)
        end
    end
    return true
end

local function uninstall(pkg)
    print("Uninstalling " .. pkg.name .. " " .. pkg.version)
    for i = 1, #pkg.files do
        local path = pkg.dst .. pkg.files[i]
        if fs.exists(path) then
            print("- " .. path)
            fs.delete(path)
        else
            print("? " .. path)
        end
    end
    fs.delete(PKG_PATH .. "/" .. pkg.name)
end

local function listPackages()
    local items = fs.list(PKG_PATH)
    if #items == 0 then
        print("No packages installed")
        return
    end
    print("Installed packages: ")
    for i = 1, #items do
        local pkg = getLocalPkg(items[i])
        print(pkg.name .. " " .. pkg.version)
    end
end

local function help()
    print("usage:")
    print("  pkg install <package>")
    print("  pkg uninstall <package>")
    print("  pkg list")
end

local commands={
    install=function(args)
        if #args ~= 1 then
            return help()
        end
        local pkgId = args[1]
        checkDir()
        local pkg = getRemotePkg(pkgId)
        local localPkg = getLocalPkg(pkg.name)
        if localPkg ~= nil then
            uninstall(localPkg)
        end
        if canInstall(pkg) then
            install(pkg)
        else
            print("Cannot install " .. pkg.name)
        end
    end,
    uninstall=function(args)
        local name = args[1]
        local pkg = getLocalPkg(name)
        if pkg == nil then
            print(pkg .. " is not installed")
        else
            uninstall(pkg)
        end
    end,
    list=listPackages,
    help=help
}

local args={...}
local command=table.remove(args, 1)
if commands[command] ~= nil then
    commands[command](args)
else
    commands.help(args)
end

from datetime import date as date_type, timedelta
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
import pyspark.sql.functions as F


spark_session = SparkSession \
    .builder \
    .master("yarn") \
    .config("spark.driver.cores", "2") \
    .config("spark.driver.memory", "2g") \
    .appName("tag_tops") \
    .getOrCreate()


def input_paths(date: date_type, depth: int, event_type: str = 'message'):
    base_prod_events_path = "/user/sergeaver/data/events"
    date_obj = date_type.fromisoformat(date)
    paths = []
    for day in range(depth):
        date_in_past = (date_obj - timedelta(days=day)).strftime("%Y-%m-%d")
        paths.append(f"{base_prod_events_path}/date={date_in_past}/event_type={event_type}")
    return paths


def reaction_tag_tops(spark: SparkSession, date: date_type, depth: int):
    paths = input_paths(date, depth)
    messages = spark.read.parquet(*paths)
    reaction_paths = input_paths(date, depth, 'reaction')
    reactions = spark.read.parquet(*reaction_paths)
    all_reactions = reactions \
        .select(F.col("event.message_id").alias("message_id"),
                F.col("event.reaction_type").alias("reaction"),
                F.col("event.reaction_from").alias("user_id"))
        
    all_tags = messages \
        .where("event.message_channel_to is not null") \
        .select(F.col("event.message_id").alias("message_id"),
                F.col("event.message_from").alias("user_id"),
                F.explode(F.col("event.tags")).alias("tag"))\
        .groupBy("user_id", "tag", "message_id") \
        .agg(F.expr("count(tag) as tag_count")).orderBy(F.col("tag_count").desc(), F.desc("tag"))
    df = all_reactions.join(all_tags.select("message_id", "tag"), "message_id").cache()
    window = Window().partitionBy(["user_id", "reaction"]).orderBy(F.desc("tag_count"), F.desc("tag"))
    df_window = df.groupBy("user_id", "tag", "reaction") \
                  .agg(F.count("*").alias("tag_count")) \
                  .withColumn("rank", F.row_number().over(window)) \
                  .filter(F.col('rank') <= 3) \
                  .groupBy('user_id', "reaction") \
                  .pivot('rank') \
                  .agg({'tag': 'first'})
    liked = df_window.where(F.col("reaction") == "like") \
                     .withColumnRenamed('1', 'like_tag_top_1') \
                     .withColumnRenamed('2', 'like_tag_top_2') \
                     .withColumnRenamed('3', 'like_tag_top_3') \
                     .select("user_id", "like_tag_top_1", "like_tag_top_2", "like_tag_top_3")
    disliked = df_window.where(F.col("reaction") == "dislike") \
                        .withColumnRenamed('1', 'dislike_tag_top_1') \
                        .withColumnRenamed('2', 'dislike_tag_top_2') \
                        .withColumnRenamed('3', 'dislike_tag_top_3') \
                        .select("user_id", "dislike_tag_top_1", "dislike_tag_top_2", "dislike_tag_top_3")
    df_joined = liked.join(disliked, ['user_id'], how='full_outer')
    return df_joined

return {
	function()
		local fold = Instance.new("Folder", workspace)
		fold.Name = "__HOLDER"
		local memor = game:GetService('Stats'):GetTotalMemoryUsageMb()
		repeat
			local part = Instance.new("Part", fold)
			part.Shape = Enum.PartType.Ball
			part.Anchored = true
			part.Name = "_Part"
			part.Position = Vector3.new(9e9,9e9,9e9)
			part.Size = Vector3.new(100, 100, 100)
			task.wait(.1)
		until game:GetService('Stats'):GetTotalMemoryUsageMb() - memor >= 20
	end,
	function()
		for i, v in pairs(workspace["__HOLDER"]:GetChildren()) do
			if v:IsA("BasePart") and v.Name == "_Part" then
				v:Destroy()
			end
		end
	end
}

content:
"""
W tym zadaniu rozważamy binarny zapis liczb całkowitych dodatnich.
Blokiem w zapisie binarnym liczby nazywamy każdy niepusty, maksymalny (nie można go
rozszerzyć ani z lewej, ani z prawej strony) ciąg kolejnych takich samych cyfr w tym zapisie.
Przykład:
Liczba binarna 111110000110111 składa się z pięciu bloków – trzech bloków złożonych
z jedynek (11111, 11 i 111) i dwóch bloków złożonych z zer (0000 i 0).
Liczba binarna 1111111111111111 składa się z jednego bloku złożonego z jedynek.
"""


def ex_2_1():
    # with open("bin.txt", "r") as f:
    # content = f.read().splitlines()

    # [67, 245]
    content = ["1000011", "11110101"]
    for number in content:
        zeros = number.split("1")
        ones = number.split("0")
        numbers = zeros + ones
        counter = len([i for i in numbers if i != ""])
        print(counter)


# print(ex_2_1())
# 3
# 5

"""
Podaj, ile liczb w pliku bin.txt składa się z co najwyżej dwóch bloków (zgodnie
z definicją bloku podaną wcześniej).
Dla danych z pliku bin_przyklad.txt poprawna odpowiedź to 3.
"""


def ex_2_2():
    with open("bin_przyklad.txt", "r") as f:
        content = f.read().splitlines()
    counter = 0
    for number in content:
        zeros = number.split("1")
        ones = number.split("0")
        numbers = zeros + ones
        numbers_length = len([i for i in numbers if i != ""])
        if numbers_length <= 2:
            counter += 1
    print(counter)


# print(ex_2_2())
# 3

"""
Wypisz największą z liczb zapisanych w pliku bin.txt.
Dla danych z pliku bin_przyklad.txt poprawna odpowiedź to
10001111110111100000.
"""


def ex_2_3():
    with open("bin_przyklad.txt", "r") as f:
        content = f.read().splitlines()
    max_number = 0
    for number in content:
        number = int(number, 2)
        if number > max_number:
            max_number = number
    return bin(max_number)[2:]


# print(ex_2_3())
# 10001111110111100000


"""
Napisz program, który dla każdej binarnej liczby p zapisanej w pliku bin.txt obliczy
wynik działania
p XOR (p div 2)
gdzie XOR to operacja bitowa opisana wcześniej, a p div 2 oznacza połowę liczby p,
zaokrągloną w dół do liczby całkowitej.0–1–
2–3
Otrzymane wyniki podaj w systemie binarnym. Zapisz je do pliku wyniki2_5.txt
w kolejności występowania liczb w pliku bin.txt, każdy wynik w oddzielnym wierszu.
Odpowiedź dla danych z pliku bin_
"""


def ex_2_4():
    with open("bin_przyklad.txt", "r") as f:
        content = f.read().splitlines()
    for number in content:
        number = int(number, 2)
        number = number ^ (number // 2)
        print(bin(number)[2:])


print(ex_2_4())

"""
10000
100001011
1001000
1000010000
11001000001100010000
1000001000110000
111

niżej są same 111
"""

-- Initialize the vehicle transmission
function initTransmission(vehicle)
    -- Set the vehicle settings
    local maxSpeeds = { 0, 60, 100, 140 }
    local maxRPMs = { 0, 4000, 6000, 8000 }
    local neutralSpeedLimit = 5
    local neutralRPMLimit = 1200
    local gearSpeedRatios = { 0, 0.5, 0.8, 1.2 }
    local gearRPMRatios = { 0, 0.5, 0.8, 1.2 }
    local gearChangeSpeedCoefficients = { 1.2, 1.1, 1.0, 0.8 }
    local clutchEngagementSpeed = 10

    -- Initialize the vehicle data table
    setElementData(vehicle, "vehicleData", {
        currentGear = 1,
        currentRPM = 0,
        currentSpeed = 0,
        gearChanging = false,
        clutchEngaged = false,
        numberOfGears = #maxSpeeds - 1,
        maxVelocity = maxSpeeds[1],
        maxRPMs = maxRPMs,
        neutralSpeedLimit = neutralSpeedLimit,
        neutralRPMLimit = neutralRPMLimit,
        gearSpeedRatios = gearSpeedRatios,
        gearRPMRatios = gearRPMRatios,
        gearChangeSpeedCoefficients = gearChangeSpeedCoefficients,
        clutchEngagementSpeed = clutchEngagementSpeed,
        clutchDisengagementSpeed = clutchEngagementSpeed
    }, false)
end

-- Update the vehicle data every tick
function updateVehicleData()
    for _, vehicle in ipairs(getElementsByType("vehicle")) do
        local vehicleData = vehicle:getData("vehicleData")
        if vehicleData then
            local currentGear = vehicleData.currentGear
            local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
            local currentSpeed = vehicle:getSpeed()

            -- Update the current RPM and speed
            vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
            vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

            -- Update the maximum speed based on the current gear
            local maxSpeed = vehicle:getMaxVelocity(currentGear)
            vehicleData.maxVelocity = maxSpeed

            -- Update the current gear if the RPM or speed is out of range
            if currentRPM > vehicleData.maxRPMs[currentGear] or currentSpeed > maxSpeed or currentSpeed < -maxSpeed then
                shiftGear(vehicle, "up")
            elseif currentGear > 1 and currentSpeed < vehicleData.neutralSpeedLimit and currentRPM < vehicleData.neutralRPMLimit then
                shiftGear(vehicle, "down")
            end

            -- Update the clutch engagement status
            if vehicleData.clutchEngaged and currentSpeed < vehicleData.clutchDisengagementSpeed then
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false
            end
        end
    end
end

-- Handle the gear shifting
function shiftGear(vehicle, direction)
    local vehicleData = vehicle:getData("vehicleData")
    if not vehicleData.gearChanging then
        local currentGear = vehicleData.currentGear
        local numberOfGears = vehicleData.numberOfGears

        if direction == "up" and currentGear < numberOfGears then
            vehicleData.gearChanging = true
            setTimer(function()
                if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                    return
                end

                localtargetGear = currentGear + 1
                local gearSpeedRatio = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatios[targetGear]
                local gearRPMRatio = vehicleData.gearRPMRatios[targetGear]
                local gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficients[currentGear]

                -- Engage the clutch
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = true

                -- Increase the RPM and speed gradually
                local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
                local targetRPM = vehicleData.maxRPMs[targetGear] * gearRPMRatio
                local targetSpeed = vehicleData.maxVelocity * gearSpeedRatio
                local acceleration = (targetSpeed - vehicleData.currentSpeed) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                local currentSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed

                setTimer(function()
                    if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                        return
                    end

                    currentRPM = currentRPM + (targetRPM - currentRPM) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                    currentSpeed = currentSpeed + acceleration
                    vehicle:setRPM(currentRPM)
                    vehicle:setSpeed(currentSpeed)
                    vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
                    vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

                    -- Disengage the clutch
                    vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false

                    -- Update the current gear
                    vehicleData.currentGear = targetGear
                    vehicleData.gearChanging = false
                end, 1000, gearChangeSpeedCoefficient)
            end, 500, 1)
        elseif direction == "down" and currentGear > 1 then
            vehicleData.gearChanging = true
            setTimer(function()
                if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                    return
                end

                local targetGear = currentGear - 1
                local gearSpeedRatio = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatios[targetGear]
                local gearRPMRatio = vehicleData.gearRPMRatios[targetGear]
                local gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficients[targetGear]

                -- Engage the clutch
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = true

                -- Decrease the RPM and speed gradually
                local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
                local targetRPM = vehicleData.maxRPMs[targetGear] * gearRPMRatio
                local targetSpeed = vehicleData.maxVelocity * gearSpeedRatio
                local deceleration = (vehicleData.currentSpeed - targetSpeed) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                local currentSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed

                setTimer(function()
                    if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                        return
                    end

                    currentRPM = currentRPM - (currentRPM - targetRPM) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                    currentSpeed = currentSpeed - deceleration
                    vehicle:setRPM(currentRPM)
                    vehicle:setSpeed(currentSpeed)
                    vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
                    vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

                    -- Disengage the clutch
                    vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false

                    -- Update the current gear
                    vehicleData.currentGear = targetGear
                    vehicleData.gearChanging = false
                end, 1000, gearChangeSpeedCoefficient)
            end, 500, 1)
        elseif direction == "reverse" and currentGear == 1 then
            vehicleData.gearChanging = true
            setTimer(function()
                if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                    return
                end

                local targetGear = #vehicleData.maxRPMs
                local gearSpeedRatio = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatios[targetGear]
                local gearRPMRatio = vehicleData.gearRPMRatios[targetGear]
                local gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficients[targetGear]

                -- Engage the clutch
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = true

                -- Decrease the speed gradually
                local currentSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed
                local targetSpeed = -vehicleData.maxVelocity * gearSpeedRatio
                local deceleration = (vehicleData.currentSpeed - targetSpeed) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient

                setTimer(function()
                    if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                        return
                    end

                    currentSpeed = currentSpeed - deceleration
                    vehicle:setSpeed(currentSpeed)
                    vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

                    -- Disengage the clutch
                    vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false

                    -- Update the current gear
                    vehicleData.currentGear = targetGear
                    vehicleData.gearChanging = false
                end, 1000, gearChangeSpeedCoefficient)
            end, 500, 1)
        end

end

-- Handle the gear shifting
function shiftGear(vehicle, direction)
    local vehicleData = vehicle:getData("vehicleData")
    if not vehicleData.gearChanging then
        local currentGear = vehicleData.currentGear
        local numberOfGears = vehicleData.numberOfGears

        if direction == "up" and currentGear < numberOfGears then
            vehicleData.gearChanging = true
            setTimer(function()
                if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                    return
                end

                local targetGear = currentGear + 1
                local gearSpeedRatio = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatios[targetGear]
                local gearRPMRatio = vehicleData.gearRPMRatios[targetGear]
                local gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficients[currentGear]

                -- Engage the clutch
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = true

                -- Calculate the target RPM and speed based on the gear ratios
                local maxRPM = vehicleData.maxRPMs[targetGear]
                local maxVelocity = vehicleData.maxVelocity * gearSpeedRatio
                local targetRPM = maxRPM * gearRPMRatio
                local targetSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed +
                    (maxVelocity - vehicleData.maxVelocity) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient

                -- Gradually increase the RPM and speed
                local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
                local acceleration = (targetSpeed - vehicleData.currentSpeed) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                local currentSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed

                setTimer(function()
                    if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                        return
                    end

                    -- Increase the RPM and speed
                    currentRPM = currentRPM + (targetRPM - currentRPM) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                    currentSpeed = currentSpeed + acceleration

                    -- Update the vehicle data
                    vehicle:setRPM(currentRPM)
                    vehicle:setSpeed(currentSpeed)
                    vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
                    vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

                    -- Disengage the clutch
                    vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false

                    -- Update the current gear
                    vehicleData.currentGear = targetGear
                    vehicleData.gearChanging = false
                end, 1000, gearChangeSpeedCoefficient)
            end, 500, 1)
        elseif direction == "down" and currentGear > 1 then
            vehicleData.gearChanging = true
            setTimer(function()
                if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                    return
                end

                local targetGear = currentGear - 1
                local gearSpeedRatio = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatios[targetGear]
                local gearRPMRatio = vehicleData.gearRatios[targetGear]
                local gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficients[targetGear]

                -- Engage the clutch
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = true

                -- Calculate the target RPM and speed based on the gear ratios
                local maxRPM = vehicleData.maxRPMs[targetGear]
                local maxVelocity = vehicleData.maxVelocity * gearSpeedRatio
                local targetRPM = maxRPM * gearRPMRatio
                local targetSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed -
                    (vehicleData.maxVelocity - maxVelocity) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient

                -- Gradually decrease the RPM and speed
                local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
                local deceleration = (vehicleData.currentSpeed - targetSpeed) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                local currentSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed

                setTimer(function()
                    if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                        return
                    end

                    -- Decrease the RPM and speed
                    currentRPM = currentRPM - (currentRPM - targetRPM) / gearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                    currentSpeed = currentSpeed - dec

                    -- Update the vehicle data
                    vehicle:setRPM(currentRPM)
                    vehicle:setSpeed(currentSpeed)
                    vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
                    vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

                    -- Disengage the clutch
                    vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false

                    -- Update the current gear
                    vehicleData.currentGear = targetGear
                    vehicleData.gearChanging = false
                end, 1000, gearChangeSpeedCoefficient)
            end, 500, 1)
        elseif direction == "reverse" and currentGear == 1 then
            -- Handle the shift to reverse gear
            vehicleData.gearChanging = true
            setTimer(function()
                if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                    return
                end

                -- Engage the clutch
                vehicleData.clutchEngaged = true

                -- Set the target gear and speed
                local targetGear = 0 -- Reverse gear
                local targetSpeed = -vehicleData.reverseMaxVelocity

                -- Gradually decrease the speed
                local deceleration = (vehicleData.currentSpeed - targetSpeed) /
                    vehicleData.reverseGearChangeSpeedCoefficient
                local currentSpeed = vehicleData.currentSpeed

                setTimer(function()
                    if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                        return
                    end

                    currentSpeed = currentSpeed - deceleration

                    -- Update the vehicle data
                    vehicle:setSpeed(currentSpeed)
                    vehicleData.currentSpeed = currentSpeed

                    -- Disengage the clutch
                    vehicleData.clutchEngaged = false

                    -- Update the current gear
                    vehicleData.currentGear = targetGear
                    vehicleData.gearChanging = false
                end, 1000, vehicleData.reverseGearChangeSpeedCoefficient)
            end, 500, 1)
        end
    end
end

-- Handle the clutch
function handleClutch(vehicle)
    local vehicleData = vehicle:getData("vehicleData")
    if vehicleData.clutchEngaged then
        -- Decrease the RPM gradually
        local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
        local targetRPM = vehicleData.minRPMs[vehicleData.currentGear]
        local deceleration = (currentRPM - targetRPM) / vehicleData.clutchChangeSpeedCoefficient

        setTimer(function()
            if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                return
            end

            currentRPM = currentRPM - deceleration
            vehicle:setRPM(currentRPM)
            vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
        end, 1000, vehicleData.clutchChangeSpeedCoefficient)
    else
        -- Increase the RPM gradually
        local currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()
        local targetRPM = vehicleData.maxRPMs[vehicleData.currentGear]
        local acceleration = (targetRPM - currentRPM) / vehicleData.clutchChangeSpeedCoefficient

        setTimer(function()
            if not isElement(vehicle) or not vehicle:getOccupant() or not vehicleData then
                return
            end

            currentRPM = currentRPM + acceleration
            vehicle:setRPM(currentRPM)
            vehicleData.currentRPM = currentRPM
        end, 1000, vehicleData.clutchChangeSpeedCoefficient)
    end
end

-- Update the vehicle data
function updateVehicleData(vehicle)
    local vehicleData = vehicle:getData("vehicleData")
    if not vehicleData then
        return
    end

    -- Update the current speed and RPM
    vehicleData.currentSpeed = vehicle:getSpeed()
    vehicleData.currentRPM = vehicle:getRPM()

    -- Update the gear ratios based on the current gear
    local currentGear = vehicleData.currentGear
    vehicleData.gearSpeedRatio = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatios[currentGear]
    vehicleData.gearRPMRatio = vehicleData.gearRPMRatios[currentGear]

    -- Update the min and max RPMs based on the current gear
    vehicleData.minRPM = vehicleData.minRPMs[currentGear]
    vehicleData.maxRPM = vehicleData.maxRPMs[currentGear]

    -- Update thegear change speed coefficient based on the clutch state
    if vehicleData.clutchEngaged then
        vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.clutchChangeSpeedCoefficient
    elseif vehicleData.currentGear == 0 then
        vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.reverseGearChangeSpeedCoefficient
    else
        vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = vehicleData.gearChangeSpeedCoefficients[vehicleData.currentGear]
    end
end

-- Hook the events
addEventHandler("onVehicleStartEnter", root, function(player, seat)
    if seat == 0 then
        -- Initialize the vehicle data
        local vehicleData = {
            numberOfGears = 5,
            gearSpeedRatios = { 0, 2.66, 1.78, 1.3, 1, 0.84 },
            gearRPMRatios = { 0, 0.5, 0.7, 0.85, 1, 1.15 },
            gearChangeSpeedCoefficients = { 0.4, 0.5, 0.6, 0.7, 0.8, 0.9 },
            reverseMaxVelocity = 5,
            reverseGearChangeSpeedCoefficient = 0.6,
            clutchChangeSpeedCoefficient = 0.05,
            currentGear = 1,
            currentSpeed = 0,
            currentRPM = 0,
            clutchEngaged = false,
            gearChanging = false,
            gearSpeedRatio = 2.66,
            gearRPMRatio = 0.5,
            minRPMs = { 0, 1000, 1500, 2000, 2500, 3000 },
            maxRPMs = { 0, 4000, 4500, 5000, 5500, 6000 },
            minRPM = 1000,
            maxRPM = 4000,
            gearChangeSpeedCoefficient = 0.4,
        }
        player:setData("vehicleData", vehicleData)
    end
end)

addEventHandler("onVehicleEnter", root, function(player, seat)
    if seat == 0 then
        -- Start the vehicle engine
        local vehicleData = player:getData("vehicleData")
        if not vehicleData then
            return
        end

        local vehicle = source
        vehicle:setEngineState(true)
        updateVehicleData(vehicle)
    end
end)

addEventHandler("onVehicleExit", root, function(player, seat)
    if seat == 0 then
        -- Stop the vehicle engine
        local vehicle = source
        vehicle:setEngineState(false)
    end
end)

addEventHandler("onVehicleUpdate", root, function(dt)
    -- Update the vehicle data
    local vehicle = source
    updateVehicleData(vehicle)

    -- Handlethe clutch and gear changing
    local vehicleData = vehicle:getData("vehicleData")
    if not vehicleData then
        return
    end

    if not vehicleData.clutchEngaged and not vehicleData.gearChanging then
        -- Calculate the target speed based on the throttle and gear ratios
        local throttle = vehicle:getThrottle()
        local targetSpeed = vehicleData.gearSpeedRatio * throttle * vehicleData.maxSpeed

        -- Calculate the target RPM based on the target speed and gear ratios
        local targetRPM = vehicleData.gearRPMRatio * targetSpeed / vehicleData.wheelRadius

        -- Update the RPM
        if vehicleData.currentRPM < targetRPM then
            local acceleration = (targetRPM - vehicleData.currentRPM) / vehicleData.accelerationTime
            vehicleData.currentRPM = math.min(targetRPM, vehicleData.currentRPM + acceleration * dt)
        elseif vehicleData.currentRPM > targetRPM then
            local deceleration = (vehicleData.currentRPM - targetRPM) / vehicleData.decelerationTime
            vehicleData.currentRPM = math.max(targetRPM, vehicleData.currentRPM - deceleration * dt)
        end

        -- Update the speed
        if vehicleData.currentSpeed < targetSpeed then
            local acceleration = (targetSpeed - vehicleData.currentSpeed) / vehicleData.accelerationTime
            vehicleData.currentSpeed = math.min(targetSpeed, vehicleData.currentSpeed + acceleration * dt)
        elseif vehicleData.currentSpeed > targetSpeed then
            local deceleration = (vehicleData.currentSpeed - targetSpeed) / vehicleData.decelerationTime
            vehicleData.currentSpeed = math.max(targetSpeed, vehicleData.currentSpeed - deceleration * dt)
        end

        -- Handle the clutch
        handleClutch(vehicle)

        -- Handle the gear changing
        handleGearChanging(vehicle)
    end
end)

[project]
name = 'my_project'
version = '0.0.1'
readme = 'README.md'
requires-python = '==3.10.*'

[tool.ruff]
select = [
    'E', 'F', 'W', 'C90', 'I', 'N', 'UP', 'YTT', 'S', 'BLE',
    'B', 'C4', 'DTZ', 'DJ', 'FA', 'ISC', 'ICN', 'G', 'PIE',
    'T20', 'PYI', 'PT', 'Q', 'RSE', 'RET', 'SIM', 'TID',
    'TCH', 'INT', 'PTH', 'TD', 'ERA', 'PL'
]
line-length = 120
target-version = 'py310'
ignore = ['E501', 'S101', 'DJ001']

[tool.ruff.per-file-ignores]
"__init__.py" = ['F401']
"**/migrations/**.py" = ['Q000']

[tool.ruff.flake8-pytest-style]
fixture-parentheses = false

[tool.ruff.flake8-quotes]
inline-quotes = 'single'

[tool.ruff.pylint]
max-args = 8

[tool.black]
line-length = 120
target-version = ['py310']
skip-string-normalization = true

[tool.isort]
profile = 'black'
multi_line_output = 3
include_trailing_comma = true
force_grid_wrap = 0
use_parentheses = true
ensure_newline_before_comments = true
line_length = 120
known_third_party = [
    'celery', 'django', 'django_filters', 'drf_spectacular', 'environs', 'pytest',
    'requests', 'rest_framework', 'rest_framework_filters', 'sentry_sdk'
]

[tool.pytest.ini_options]
env_override_existing_values = 1
env_files = ['.env', '.env-test']
DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE = 'my_project.settings'
markers = ['slow: marks tests as slow (deselect with -m "not slow")']
python_files = ['tests.py', 'test_*.py', '*_tests.py']
log_level = 'CRITICAL'
log_format = '{"process":"%(process)d","thread":"%(thread)d","name":"%(name)s","levelname":"%(levelname)s","message":%(message)s}'
usefixtures = ['_configure_structlog', 'db']

[tool.coverage.run]
branch = true
omit = ['*/site-packages/*', '*/bin/*', 'manage.py', '*/migrations/*']

[tool.coverage.report]
exclude_lines = ['pragma: no cover', 'def __str__', 'def __repr__', 'if settings.DEBUG', 'if TYPE_CHECKING']

[tool.mypy]
python_version = '3.10'

ignore_missing_imports = true
warn_unused_configs = true
warn_redundant_casts = true
warn_unused_ignores = true
no_implicit_optional = true
strict_equality = true
strict_concatenate = true
check_untyped_defs = true
disallow_subclassing_any = true
disallow_untyped_decorators = true
disallow_any_generics = true
disallow_untyped_calls = true
disallow_incomplete_defs = true
disallow_untyped_defs = true
no_implicit_reexport = true
warn_return_any = true
warn_unreachable = true
warn_no_return = false

plugins = ['mypy_django_plugin.main', 'mypy_drf_plugin.main']

[tool.django-stubs]
django_settings_module = 'my_project.settings'

You can change this as necessary. # # Words and phrases below quote translations by Edwin Morgan of Balestrini. # # Wayne Clements, www.in-vacua.com. email: invacua_at__btinternet[Do T]com # ############################### print "Content-type: text/html\n\n"; srand; my @array = ("Of the streets that fade in the setting sun ", "there must be one (which one, I can't say) ", "that I've already walked for the very last time ", "unaware of the secret limits I obey ", "There must be someone whose almighty rule ", "causes this hidden order to be fixed ", "someone who weaves and then unravels ", "the dreamlike shadows with which life is mixed ", # Limits by Jorge Luis Borges: "I wandered lonely as a cloud ", "That floats on high o'er vales and hills ", "When all at once I saw a crowd ", "A host, of golden daffodils ", "Beside the lake, beneath the trees ", "Fluttering and dancing in the breeze ", "Continuous as the stars that shine ", "And twinkle on the milky way ", "They stretched in never-ending line ", "Along the margin of a bay ", "Ten thousand saw I at a glance ", "Tossing their heads in sprightly dance ", # I Wandered Lonely as a Cloud By William Wordsworth: "Perhaps one morning walking in dry glassy air ", "I will turn, I will see the miracle complete ", "nothingness at my shoulder, the void behind ", "me, with a drunkard's terror ", "Then, as on a screen, trees houses hills ", "will advance swiftly in familiar illusion ", "But it will be too late; and I will return, silently ", "to men who do not look back, with my secret"); # Perhaps One Morning Walking by Montale: ## example stanza # 0 1 # Hair between lips, || they all return
# 2 # to their roots || in the blinding fireball ||
# 3 4 # I envision their return || until he moves his fingers # 5 # slowly || and although things flourish || # 6 7 # takes on the well known mushroom shape || endeavouring # 8 # to grasp || while the multitude of things come into being. # my %seen = (); $seen{int(rand(@array))}++ while scalar keys %seen<24; #a random group of lines will be chosen my @select = @array[keys %seen]; shuffle(\@select); $select[0] = ucfirst($select[0]); # cap first line (my $last0) = $select[0] =~ /(\s*\S+)\s*$/; $select[0] =~ s/\Q$last0/$last0,/; # add comma (my $nth) = $select[1] =~ /(?:\w+\W+){1}(\w+)/; $select[1] =~ s/$nth/$nth

findLast :: Eq a => a -> [a] -> Int
findLast element lst = findLastHelper element lst (-1) 0
        where
            findLastHelper :: Eq a => a -> [a] -> Int -> Int -> Int
            findLastHelper _ [] lastIndex _ = lastIndex
            findLastHelper element (x:xs) lastIndex count = 
              if x == element
                then findLastHelper element xs count (count + 1)
                else findLastHelper element xs lastIndex (count + 1)

findFirst :: Eq a => a -> [a] -> Int
findFirst element lst = findFirstHelper element lst (-1) 0
        where
            findFirstHelper :: Eq a => a -> [a] -> Int -> Int -> Int
            findFirstHelper _ [] _ _ = -1
            findFirstHelper element (x:xs) firstIndex count
              | x == element = count
              | otherwise = findFirstHelper element xs firstIndex (count + 1)

main = do
        let lst = [1, 2, 3, 4, 3, 2, 1]
            element = 3

        putStrLn "Lista: "
        print lst

        putStrLn "Indeks ostatniego wystapienia:"
        print (findLast element lst)

        putStrLn "Indeks pierwszego wystapienia:"
        print (findFirst element lst)
